@217 = ~One essay from an anonymous scholar catches your eye as it has been preserved in its entirety. Its insight into the nature of the necromantic arts is considerable.~
@218 = ~The vast amount of dark knowledge absorbed from the book left its mark on your soul and forces you to reconsider your own perspective on the concepts of good and evil.~
@219 = ~Reading the introductory passage about the ritual makes it clear very quickly that the summoner must either provide or contain a strong link to supernatural forces. You can't meet either of the requirements.~
@220 = ~As you read the introductory passage about the ritual, it quickly becomes apparent that the summoner must either provide or contain a strong link to supernatural forces. As a child of Bhaal you would apparently meet that requirement.~
@221 = ~Oh no, there is no way in hell I'd even consider it. Having odd dreams about Bhaal is bad enough.~
@222 = ~The preparatory paragraph goes into more detail what is required to successfully perform the ritual. The summoner must surrender a good portion of their spiritual essence to ensure the aid of the demon.~
