// dialog: Lazarus Librarus
@500 = ~I have an unusual request. We have found a tome written in unknown runes that resists any attempts of magical identification. Would you be willing to translate it?~
@501 = ~I can certainly try. Let me take a look.~
@502 = ~Ah, by all the powers! Please cover it immediately! The tome is written in abyssal runes and probably heavily enchanted. Even glancing at it could have a profound effect on the reader.~
@503 = ~I cannot possibly fulfill your request. The tome should be destroyed or lock away as quickly as possible.~
@504 = ~What are you so afraid of?~
@505 = ~In case you're not aware, these kinds of runes always carry a bit of the abyssal powers with them. Simply reading the runes may corrupt the minds of unwitting readers who didn't take the necessary precautions.~
@506 = ~Maybe you are right. What exactly do you suggest?~
@507 = ~I could cast a powerful spell, similarly to Imprisonment, that will transport the tome to a miniature pocket dimension where it hopefully won't be discovered for a long time.~
@508 = ~Since it poses a considerable threat to everyone, I would even do it for free.~
@509 = ~Alright, please cast your spell.~
@510 = ~On second thought, I'd like to take the risk. Can you please tell me a way how to translate it myself?~
@511 = ~Absolutely not. I don't want to be responsible for guiding someone to their certain doom.~
@512 = ~However, since your very being is already touched by supernatural forces I can give you the advice to seek out members of the demonic races, namely the denizens of the Abyss or the Nine Hells.~
@513 = ~Thank you for your help.~
@514 = ~No, don't thank me for that. If you value your life then lock the tome away and never touch it again.~
@515 = ~You won't dissuade me from it. Can't you help me at all?~
@516 = ~Let me prepare the spell.~
@517 = ~I reconsidered and want to have the demonic tome locked away. Can you do it?~
@518 = ~I'm relieved that you changed your mind. Yes, I can do that, and gladly so. Please hand me the tome.~
@519 = ~Here you are.~
@520 = ~They possess the necessary knowledge to help you, provided you can pay their services.~
@521 = ~It is done. The tome rests now in a safe location. At least for a while. Artifacts like that have a tendency to reappear eventually.~

@550 = ~The spell pulls the tome out of the pocket dimension where it was locked away and drops it to the ground. You quickly pick it up and put it in your inventory.~

